'''Fawaz Hussain''' or '''Fawaz Husên''' (born 1953), is a contemporary Kurdish writer and translator. He was born in northeastern Syria. He pursued his studies in [[University of Paris|Sorbonne]] from 1978 to 1992, and received PhD in French language and literature in 1988. He is a member of Swedish Writers' Union and French Writers' Syndicate. In addition to Kurdish, he has written several books in French and has translated works of [[Albert Camus]] and [[Antoine de Saint-Exupéry|Saint–Exupéry]] into Kurdish.<ref name="Carmichael">{{cite news|url=http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/210920151|title=Exiled by war, writer carries on his love affair with Kurdish|last=Carmichael|first=Salwa Nakhoul|date=21 September 2015|work=Rudaw|accessdate=15 December 2015}}</ref>

