{{Orphan|date=April 2014}}

'''Gerda Helena Wrede-Paischeff''' (26 November 1896 &ndash; 17 November 1967), better known as '''Gerda Wrede''', was a [[Finnish people|Finnish]] actor and [[speech therapist]].<ref name=UF/>

Born in [[Piikkiö]], Gerda Wrede attended the [[Swedish Theatre]]'s acting school in [[Helsinki]] between 1914 and 1916. After finishing her training, she worked at the theatre as an actor until 1921, and then again from 1927 to 1928. In 1931, she became the acting director of the school, and was promoted to the position of principal in 1941.<ref name=UF/>

She was the aunt of the film and theatre director [[Caspar Wrede]].<ref name="HDSC">{{cite book|editor=John Sundholm|others=et al.|title=Historical Dictionary of Scandinavian Cinema|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QktG6a4YnQYC&pg=PA414|year=2012|publisher=Scarecrow Press|isbn=978-0-8108-7899-0|page=414}}</ref>

