{{infobox language |name=Himarimã |nativename=Hi-Merima |states=Brazil |region=[[Tapauá River]] valley |ethnicity=[[Hi-Merimã people]] |speakers=40 |date=no date |ref=e15 |familycolor=American |family=unattested; [[Arawan languages|Arawan]]? |iso3=hir |glotto=hima1247 |glottorefname=Himarima }}
'''Himarimã''' is the presumed language of the [[Uncontacted peoples|uncontacted]] [[Hi-Merimã people]] in [[Amazonas (Brazilian state)|Amazonas]], [[Brazil]],<ref name=e15/> The language is believed to be [[Arawan languages|Arawán]] per testimonies from the Suruwahá and Banawá.<ref>Hammarström (2015) Ethnologue 16/17/18th editions: a comprehensive review: online appendices</ref>
