'''Kui''' (also Kandh, Khondi, Khond, Khondo, Kanda, Kodu (Kōdu), Kodulu, Kuinga (Kūinga), Kuy) is a  South-Central [[Dravidian languages|Dravidian]] language spoken by the [[Khonds]]. It is mostly spoken in [[Odisha]], and written in the [[Odia script]]. With 641,662 registered native speakers, it figures at [[List of Indian languages by number of native speakers|rank 29]] in the 1991 [[Indian census]]. The Kui language was also referred to as the Kalinga language during the historical period.

Distinct but closely related are the [[Gondi language|Gondi]] and [[Kuvi language|Kuvi]] languages

